  "paper_analysis": {
    "summary": "This paper studies nanodiamonds from detonation and HPHT origins, comparing as-received, oxidized, and hydrogenated surfaces. By combining UV-vis, UPS, Kelvin probe, ER-EIS, FTIR, Raman, and DFT context, the authors show that surface chemistry and non-diamond carbon content strongly shift band edges, work function, electron affinity, and in-gap states; HPHT hydrogenated nanodiamonds exhibit negative electron affinity, while detonation nanodiamonds do not.",
